\begin_layout Plain Layout
\align left

\size small
Note: This figure presents residualized scatter plots of the change in the
 share of effective inventors of sector 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

 over total inventors in knowledge market 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

, over the change in the lower bound of the Herfindal-Hirschman Index for
 product market 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

, as implied by Census concentration ratios.
 The upper panel reports the data for the full sample, where both variables
 are residualized by change in log real sales and knowledge market fixed
 effects.
 The size of the markers is proportional to the weight of each observation
 in the regression (sector sales in 2012).
 The regression line uses the coefficient on the change in HHI lower bound
 in Column (2) of Table 
\size default

\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab: RegShInvHHI"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset


\size small
.
 The lower panel presents a binned scatter plot removing the observations
 with the highest 5% Mahalanobis distance from the sample centroid.
 Observations are aggregated using sales weights and the regression line
 is from Column (6) of Table 
\size default

\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab: RegShInvHHI"
plural "false"
caps "false"
