\begin_layout Plain Layout
\align left

\size small
Note: Unweighted regressions; robust standard errors in parentheses; symbols
 denote significance levels 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(+\ p<0.1,^{*}\ p<0.05,^{**}\ p<.01,^{***}\ p<.001\right)$
\end_inset

; checkmarks indicate the inclusion of fixed effects.
 This table present the results of specification (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq: spec"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

), when the outcome is the log-change in forward citations and the change
 in patent generality in sector 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

 over the change in the share of inventors employed in sector 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

.
 Column (1) and (2) presents the results when forward citations are extrapolated
 the procedure Hall et al.
 (2000) to avoid truncation bias.
 A specific cite-lag distribution over 35 years is estimated for each pair
 of cited and citing CPC2-codes.
 Column (1) employs the extrapolation scheme by each pair of CPC2 cited
 and citing sector.
 Column (2) applies the extrapolation scheme to total citations received
 by each cited patent.
 Column (3) presents results on the patent generality measures.
 All columns exclude self-citations.
 Upper panel: full sample; bottom panel: excluding sectors with absolute
 increase in the inventor share above 2%.
\end_layout

\end_inset


